definition.value: Gold nanocages, some 40 nanometers in diameter can be made by replacing the silver atoms of silver nanotubes.

label.value: carbamate ester linkage between primary amine and carbonate ester

definition.value: An explosive device comprised of carbon nanotubes. These nanoscale devices have desirable optical and thermal properties that can be exploited for novel cancer therapeutics. The ability to manipulate these properties facilitates a controlled, localized activation and clearance mechanism of diseased or abnormal cells.
